status:
Created new class “Orderer”, very much like a Peer, but since “Chain” will need to have a list of these  it should be it’s own class. Added in tracing using “debug” package. Started looking at  “Member” to allow for multiple orderers.

Status = I got 'make node-sdk-unit-tests' working on Fab06, however 'make all' does not work on Fab6.  I'm working with Greg Haskins to decide if I should open an issue for that.  I am working on my test outline for custom events

my status: checked in <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/#/c/1553/> which <@U0PB67X4K> merged on Friday. working on logging utility which will have a built in logger (based on winston) and can be replaced by one configured by the user app.
as a reminder, please see the below board for node.js SDK Sprint 3 planning: <https://jira.hyperledger.org/secure/RapidBoard.jspa?rapidView=41>
